subSubSection.paragraph:
Rostral border of cranium broad with large mesethmoid; premaxilla underneath with synchondral articulation; cranial fontanel narrow, elliptical, bounded by mesethmoid and frontal (
Fig. 11
); nasal ossified, with medial flanges partially sutured to lateral margin of mesethmoid; autopalatine tubular, oriented obliquely to longitudinal axis of body; maxilla small, shorter than autopalatine; prevomer expanded with well developed arrow-shaped lateral processes; jaws of equal size; premaxilla and dentary with three to four rows of conical teeth; first nuchal plate somewhat elliptical; second nuchal plate laterally concave, partially in contact or not with supraoccipital; third nuchal plate relatively straight, projected laterally. Epioccipital process small.

